<p style="padding:5px 0;font-family:'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-weight: 400;font-size:16px;line-height:25.6px;margin:0;">While you consider that question, Zikoko Citizen, in collaboration with TechCabal Insights, has released the <a href="https://citizen.zikoko.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2026/02/Citizen-Report-2026-e.pdf" style="text-decoration: underline;color: #b61313 !important">Citizen Report 2026</a>, a comprehensive survey of youth electoral behaviour ahead of Nigeria&rsquo;s 2027 general elections, based on responses from 10,681 people across all 36 states and the FCT.</p>
<p style="padding:5px 0;font-family:'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-weight: 400;font-size:16px;line-height:25.6px;margin:0;">As we edge closer to the moments that will define the kind of economy industries have over the next four years, it is pertinent that all eyes are on what matters: the citizens&rsquo; willpower to vote.</p>
